
Interactive: 

    It describes the way shell works for the user. 
    Its communication between user and shell. 
    Shell accepts the command from user in terminal. 
    Runs in foreground. 

Non Interactive:  

    User saves a series of commands in file (shell script) and executes after. 
    Run the commands as script.
    Runs in background. 

To create non interactive user: 
    
    useradd user-name -s /sbin/nologin 


